<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6790690-dave"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6790690-dave">Dave</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">While it is a memoir to some extent, that is only the path to help this book serve as a guide. By showing his doubts and how he overcame them, the rea<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">While it is a memoir to some extent, that is only the path to help this book serve as a guide. By showing his doubts and how he overcame them, the reader gains real insight into meditation. The "memoir" aspect actually makes it a much easier read than any other mechanism I can think of.<br /><br />If you like memoirs, enjoy this one and learn from it. If you don't like them, but are curious about meditation, this is still a worthwhile read, because you will learn a lot.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
